be\nthought of as a representation-theoretic analogue of the mentioned Chevalley\nformula. Other applications and some open problems involving \"signed crystals\"\nare discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 May 2021 09:47:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Jun 2021 04:08:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-18"}
